    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.17.11-12_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">11</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>September 19, 1936</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt, Literary Editor</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St. Louis Post-Dispatch</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Post-Dispatch Building</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St. Louis, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>In answer to your letter of September 18, I think I should say that I am primarily intersted in books dealing with speech, public speaking, rhetoric, and public affairs. During the past four years I have edited the Debate Handbook, an annual publication. The four volumes I have edited have dealt with Radio Control and Operation, Federal Aid to Education, Free Public Medicine, and Governmental Ownership of Electric Utilities. I mention the subjects because it is in these matters that I find myself interested. I am, for example, currently engaged in a study of the consumers cooperative as a possible question for nation-wide debate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                
                
                    <signed>Bower Aly</signed>
                
                    <note>BA:ak</note>
                </closer>
            
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="enclosure">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.17.11-12_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">12</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">ST. LOUIS POST-DISPATCH
                        <lb/>
                        
                    EDITORIAL DEPARTMENT</hi>
                </fw>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        St. Louis, Mo.
                        
                        September 18th
                        1  9  3  6
                    </dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Prof. Bower Aly</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>503 Stewart Rd.</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>My dear Professor Aly:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Victor Woerheide tells me that you would be interested in writing reviews for my book page on the Post-Dispatch. I am glad to know this and shall send you a book as soon as I hear from you stating the type of book you prefer.</p>
                
                <p>The number of words desired in the article will be found on the fly-leaf, and the date for delivery of copy to me as well.</p>
                
                <p>Books will be returned to the Post-Dispatch and payment will be made for articles immediately after publication<del>s</del>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very truly yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Jno. G. Neihardt</signed>
                    <signed>John G. Neihardt
                    LITERARY EDITOR</signed>
                
                    <note>JGN:EVN</note>
                </closer>
            
            </div1>
        </body>
        
